The press briefing by Press Secretary Jay Carney on December 18, 2012 covered various topics including the fiscal cliff negotiations and gun control. Carney defended the President's proposal to raise taxes on households making over $400,000, despite the President's previous promise to raise taxes on households making over $250,000. Carney emphasized that the President had demonstrated willingness to compromise and meet Republicans halfway. He also discussed the need for a balanced deficit reduction package, including revenue increases and spending cuts. Carney addressed questions about the President's stance on gun control, stating that the President supports measures such as reinstating the assault weapons ban and closing the gun show loophole. He also mentioned the need to address mental health issues, education, and other cultural factors related to gun violence. Carney did not provide specific details about the President's plans for gun control legislation or the timeline for taking action.